doc.after: Regional airliners typically seat fewer than 100 passengers and may be powered by turbofans or turboprops These airliners are the non mainline counterparts to the larger aircraft operated by the major carriers legacy carriers and flag carriers and are used to feed traffic into the large airline hubs or focus cities These particular routes may need the size of a smaller aircraft to meet the frequency needs and service levels customers expect in the marketed product that is offered by larger airlines and their modern narrow and widebody aircraft Therefore these short haul airliners are usually equipped with lavatories stand up cabins pressurization overhead storage bins reclining seats and have a flight attendant to look after the in flight needs of the passengers during Point to point transit or routes
